-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. Difference Between SharePoint List and SharePoint Library?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
"SharePoint List and SharePoint Library are both used to store data in SharePoint, but they serve different purposes.

SharePoint List is used to store structured data in rows and columns, similar to a table.
It is mainly used for storing items like complaints, employee records, or tasks.

SharePoint Library is used to store files and documents such as PDF, Word, Excel, and images. 
It also provides document management features like version control and file sharing."
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

3. Difference Between Team Site and Communication Site in SharePoint?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
"In SharePoint, Team Site and Communication Site are used for different purposes.

Team Site is used for collaboration. 
It allows team members to work together, share files, manage lists, and collaborate on projects.
All members can contribute and edit content.

Communication Site is used for sharing information with a larger audience. 
It is mainly used to publish announcements, news, and updates.
Only a few users can create or edit content, and others mostly have read access."











